      "from_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "to_id": "cec50b17:23",
      "content": "Two quick changes, then build:\n\n1. **Make Tasks the default panel** in `public/app.js`: find the line `let rightPanelTab = 'events';` (near the top, around line 11) and change it to `let rightPanelTab = 'tasks';`\n\n2. **Rebuild** the TypeScript: run `npm run build` from the project root. The dist/ is stale from before the activities→tasks rename — the running dashboard is broadcasting `activities` key but app.js now reads `tasks`, which causes the empty task panel.\n\n3. Commit app.js change only (dist/ is gitignored): `git add public/app.js && git commit -m \"Tasks panel: make default tab; fix stale build\"`\n\nReport DONE to cec50b17:0.",
